This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in computer science. The problem of dividing a cake between two bidders is a classic example in fair division, which falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.CC). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are relevant to the categories of algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with incentive compatibility, which is a key concept in mechanism design (cs.EC) and game theory (cs.GT).
